ce:section.ce:para:
As shown in Fig. 4
                        , the designed DNA probe was used to detect the miRNA-155. As the concentration of miRNA-155 increases, the fluorescence intensity at 520 nm (λem1) gradually increases, while that at 578 nm (λem2) gradually decreases, the ratio of the fluorescence intensity of the system (FD/FA) increased gradually with incremental concentration of miRNA-155 from 1.0 × 10−11 M to 1.0 × 10−8 M and showed an advisable linear relationship with the logarithm of concentration with a linear equation of FD/FA = 0.3363 Log C + 4.6739 and a squared correlation coefficient of 0.9923, where C represents the concentration of miRNA-155 in the system, FD and FA represent the fluorescence intensity of the donor (FAM) and acceptor (TAMRA), respectively. The estimated detection limit (LOD) of miRNA-155 is 1.6 × 10−12 M. In addition, we compared the proposed method with other detection strategies (Table 1
                        ). The results show that the method has high sensitivity and low detection limit, and may have the potential application in clinical biological detection.
